.md:43:  - Added migration runtime wiring to the SQLAlchemy metadata.\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:58:  - Updated the architecture notes to reflect the new SQLAlchemy and Alembic foundation.\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:60:  - Included `alembic.ini` and `migrations/` in the backend image so the migration tooling is available inside the container build context.\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:68:- shared SQLAlchemy metadata and naming conventions\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:73:That gives later prompts a stable base for repositories, services, workers, and durable job orchestration instead of forcing each prompt to invent ad hoc tables or direct SQL.\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:82:- composition and audio work are represented as durable job records\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:96:- indexes for obvious session, job, and audit queries are spelled out\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:106:### SQLAlchemy base and mixins\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:139:alembic upgrade head\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:148:alembic revision --autogenerate -m \"describe change\"\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:168:composition_job = CompositionJob(\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:170:    job_kind=CompositionJobKind.DRAFT,\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:239:./scripts/dev-compose.sh up -d postgres\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:240:./scripts/dev-compose.sh exec -T postgres psql -U storyteller -d postgres \\\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:247:  .venv/bin/alembic upgrade head\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md:249:./scripts/dev-compose.sh exec -T postgres psql -U storyteller -d storyteller_prompt11 \\\n./prompts/11-postgres