              job_id=job_id,\n./docs/contributing.md:3:Keep changes boring, typed, and easy to review. This repo is split between a React + TypeScript frontend and a FastAPI backend, so use the stack-specific tooling below instead of personal preferences.\n./docs/contributing.md:23:- Prefer names that describe product concepts directly: `session`, `pitch`, `beat_sheet`, `audio_job`.\n./docs/contributing.md:27:- Keep FastAPI route handlers thin. Parse input, call a backend-owned service, and return typed response models.\n./docs/contributing.md:30:- Treat the backend as the source of truth for workflow stage, job progress, and AI side effects. The browser reflects state; it does not own it.\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:5:from alembic import command\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:6:from alembic.config import Config\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:11:    \"audio_jobs\",\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:14:    \"composition_jobs\",\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:42:def _build_alembic_config(database_url: str) -> Config:\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:43:    config = Config(str(BACKEND_ROOT / \"alembic.ini\"))\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:67:def test_alembic_can_upgrade_from_zero_to_head_and_back(tmp_path) -> None:\n./backend/tests/test_migrations.py:70:    config = _build_alembic_config(database_url)\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:119:        job_id=\"compose-01\",\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:123:        \"sessions/session-123/composition/jobs/compose-01/segments/0007.md\"\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:127:        job_id=\"audio-job-02\",\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:130:        \"gs://storyteller-audio/sessions/session-123/audio/jobs/audio-job-02/segments/0003.mp3\"\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:134:        job_id=\"audio-job-02\",\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:138:        \"sessions/session-123/audio/jobs/audio-job-02/final/bedtime-story.mp3\"\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:167:            job_id=\"audio-job-1\",\n./backend/tests/test_storage.py:206:            job_id=\"audio-job-1\",\n./docs/product-brief.md:69:- Backend: Python, FastAPI\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:97:def test_load_session_snapshot_returns_selected_outputs_and_active_jobs(db_session) -> None:\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:237:    composition_job = CompositionJob(\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:241:        job_kind=CompositionJobKind.DRAFT,\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:246:    db_session.add(composition_job)\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:249:    audio_job = AudioJob(\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:251:        source_composition_job_id=composition_job.id,\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:259:    db_session.add(audio_job)\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:263:        composition_job_id=composition_job.id,\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:274:        audio_job_id=audio_job.id,\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:298:    assert snapshot.active_composition_job is not None\n./backend/tests/test_session_service.py:299:    assert snapshot.active_audio_job is not None\n./backend/app/services/sessions.py:305:        active_composition_job=_build_composition_job_view(aggregate.active_composition_job),\n./backend/app/services/sessions.py:306:        active_audio_job=_build_audio_job_view(aggregate.active_audio_job),\n./backend/app/services/sessions.py:459:def _build_composition_job_view(row: CompositionJob | None) -> CompositionJobView | None:\n./backend/app/services/sessions.py:465:        job_kind=row.job_kind,\n./backend/app/services/sessions.py:479:def _build_audio_job_view(row: AudioJob | None) -> AudioJobView | None:\n./docs/README.md:15:- `system-diagram.md`: one-page runtime diagram for browser, API, worker, storage, and Gemini flows\n./prompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.yolopilot.jsonlines:8:{\"color\": \"cyan\", \"emoji\": \"\\ud83d\\udee0\\ufe0f\", \"event_type\": \"Command Finished\", \"message\": \"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,240p' prompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.md\\\"\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"aggregated_output\": \"# 09 \\u2014 Initial System Diagram and First Architecture Decisions\\n\\nRead `base_prompt.md` first and preserve all prior prompt work.\\n\\n## Objective\\n\\nCapture the core architecture decisions early so later prompts can build on a stable mental model.\\n\\n## Build\\n- Write an ADR or equivalent note for the main architectural choices: backend-owned AI calls, Postgres-backed durable state, file-backed GCS emulator for assets, WebSocket-based live updates, and a separate worker process for long-running jobs.\\n- Add one lightweight system diagram in Markdown or Mermaid showing browser, API, worker, database, object storage, and Gemini integrations.\\n- Record the decision that word count, runtime, and chapter count are soft planning hints rather than hard constraints.\\n\\n## Deliverables\\n\\n- `docs/adr/` or similar notes\\n- A simple system diagram\\n- A written statement of the product\\u2019s soft-constraint philosophy\\n\\n## Acceptance checks\\n\\n- Later contributors can tell where real-time updates and long-running tasks belong.\\n- The diagram includes session resume and durable event history as first-class concepts.\\n- The architecture notes reflect the actual product brief instead of a generic app template.\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\nUse plain language. This doc is for builders, not for impressing anyone.\\n\\n## Suggested commit label\\n\\n`feat(prompt-09): initial system diagram and adr`\\n\", \"command\": \"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"sed -n '1,240p' prompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.md\\\"\", \"exit_code\": 0, \"id\": \"item_1\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"type\": \"command_execution\"}, \"type\": \"item.completed\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 8, \"prompt_index\": 10, \"prompt_name\": \"09 \\u2014 Initial System Diagram and First Architecture Decisions\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"tim