-lc './scripts/dev-compose.sh exec -T postgres psql -U storyteller -d postgres -c \\\"DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS storyteller_prompt11;\\\"'\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"aggregated_output\": \"\", \"command\": \"/bin/zsh -lc './scripts/dev-compose.sh exec -T postgres psql -U storyteller -d postgres -c \\\"DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS storyteller_prompt11;\\\"'\", \"exit_code\": null, \"id\": \"item_88\", \"status\": \"in_progress\", \"type\": \"command_execution\"}, \"type\": \"item.started\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 167, \"prompt_index\": 12, \"prompt_name\": \"11 \\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"timestap\": \"2026-03-31T22:53:38-07:00\"}\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:168:{\"color\": \"cyan\", \"emoji\": \"\\ud83d\\udee0\\ufe0f\", \"event_type\": \"Command Finished\", \"message\": \"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc './scripts/dev-compose.sh exec -T postgres psql -U storyteller -d postgres -c \\\"DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS storyteller_prompt11;\\\"'\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"aggregated_output\": \"DROP DATABASE\\n\", \"command\": \"/bin/zsh -lc './scripts/dev-compose.sh exec -T postgres psql -U storyteller -d postgres -c \\\"DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS storyteller_prompt11;\\\"'\", \"exit_code\": 0, \"id\": \"item_88\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"type\": \"command_execution\"}, \"type\": \"item.completed\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 168, \"prompt_index\": 12, \"prompt_name\": \"11 \\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"timestap\": \"2026-03-31T22:53:38-07:00\"}\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:175:{\"color\": \"green\", \"emoji\": \"\\ud83d\\udcac\", \"event_type\": \"Agent Message\", \"message\": \"Implemented the first real SQLAlchemy/Alembic persistence layer for the backend: explicit ORM models for sessions, workflow stage state, briefs, pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, story setup, composition/audio jobs, composition seg...\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"id\": \"item_92\", \"text\": \"Implemented the first real SQLAlchemy/Alembic persistence layer for the backend: explicit ORM models for sessions, workflow stage state, briefs, pitches, character sheets, beat sheets, story setup, composition/audio jobs, composition segments, export assets, and the event log, plus the initial migration at [20260331_01_initial_storyteller_schema.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/versions/20260331_01_initial_storyteller_schema.py). I also added shared DB base/session helpers, migration docs in [backend/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/README.md) and [backend/migrations/README.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/migrations/README.md), and updated the architecture/domain docs to reflect the first-schema tradeoff of tracking accepted child rows on the child tables to avoid circular foreign keys.\\n\\nVerification passed end to end: `make check`, focused backend tests, SQLite Alembic cycle tests, and a live PostgreSQL `alembic upgrade head -> downgrade base -> upgrade head` run against the compose `postgres` service. No browser checks were needed because this prompt only changed backend persistence. The required reviewer summary is written at [11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.md). Checkpoint commits: `16b904e` and `89ad342`.\", \"type\": \"agent_message\"}, \"type\": \"item.completed\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 175, \"prompt_index\": 12, \"prompt_name\": \"11 \\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"timestap\": \"2026-03-31T22:55:18-07:00\"}\n./prompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.yolopilot.jsonlines:176:{\"color\": \"bright_black\", \"emoji\": \"\\u2753\", \"event_type\": \"Unkown Event\", \"message\": \"{ \\\"item\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"item_18\\\", \\\"items\\\": [ { \\\"completed\\\": true, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Inspect existing backend patterns and derive the relational schema from the documented domain model\\\" }, { \\\"completed\\\": false, \\\"text\\\": \\\"Add SQLAlchemy models, engine/se...\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"id\": \"item_18\", \"items\": [{\"completed\": true, \"text\": \"Inspect existing backend patterns and derive the relational schema from the documented domain model\"}, {\"completed\": false, \"text\": \"Add SQLAlchemy models, engine/session helpers, and Alembic migration config for the initial schema\"}, {\"completed\": false, \"text\": \"Add targeted backend tests for metadata relationships and migration behavior from zero to head\"}, {\"completed\": false, \"text\": \"Run lint/tests/migration verification, commit checkpoints, and write the required summary file\"}], \"type\": \"todo_list\"}, \"type\": \"item.completed\"}, \"task_display_context\": {\"event_number\": 176, \"prompt_index\": 12, \"prompt_name\": \"11 \\u2014 PostgreSQL Schema and Database Migrations\", \"prompt_total\": 100}, \"timestap\": \"2026-03-31T22:55:18-07:00\"}\n./prompts/69-composition-loop-e2e-test.md:10:- Simulate a composition job with mocked model outputs and verify that progress, chunk events, and final text land in durable state correctly.\n./prompts/69-composition-loop-e2e-test.md:12:- Assert that a resumed session shows the right latest story text and job state.\n./backend/app/main.py:7:from fastapi import FastAPI\n./backend/app/main.py:26:async def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\n./backend/app/main.py:49:def create_app() -> FastAPI:\n./backend/app/main.py:57:    app = FastAPI(\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:176:        composition_job = CompositionJob(\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:180:            job_kind=CompositionJobKind.DRAFT,\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:187:            composition_job=composition_job,\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:204:        audio_job = AudioJob(\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:206:            source_composition_job=composition_job,\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:216:            audio_job=audio_job,\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:237:                composition_job,\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:240:                audio_job,\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:266:            .composition_jobs[0]\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:271:        assert session_rows[1].audio_jobs[0].status == JobStatus.COMPLETED\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:288:            \"audio_jobs\",\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:291:            \"composition_jobs\",\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:317:            \"ix_session_assets_audio_job_id_asset_kind_segment_index\",\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:318:            \"ix_session_assets_composition_job_id_asset_kind_segment_index\",\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:339:        assert asset_foreign_keys[(\"audio_job_id\",)] == \"audio_jobs\"\n./backend/tests/test_db_models.py:340:        assert asset_foreign_keys[(\"composition_job_id\",)] == \"composition_jobs\"\n./prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md:1:# 03 \u2014 Scaffold the FastAPI Backend\n./prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md:7:Initialize the backend as a FastAPI service with clear application startup, health routes, configuration loading, and room for future modules.\n./prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md:10:- Create the FastAPI app package, a health endpoint, and a versioned API router structure.\n./prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md:16:- `backend/` FastAPI project\n./prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.md:28:Prefer boring, maintainable FastAPI structure over magic.\n./docs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\n./docs/domain-model.md:33:| `active_audio_job_id` | Current audio job, if narration work is running. |\n./docs/domain-model.md:49:| `story_session` | Root aggregate for one bedtime-story project. | IDs, title, stage pointers, overall status, timestamps. | Owns the current accepted choices and job pointers. |\n./docs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\n./docs/domain-model.md:60:| `audio_job` | Parent job record for narration generation. | voice, speed, music setting, progress, status, compiled asset pointer. | Audio should be resumable and segment-aware. |\n./docs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\n./docs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\n./backend/migrations/README.md:13:- composition jobs and composition segments\n./backend/migrations/README.md:14:- audio jobs\n./backend/migrations/README.md:26:alembic upgrade head\n./backend/migrations/README.md:35:alembic downgrade base\n./backend/migrations/README.md:44:alembic revision --autogenerate -m \"describe change\"\n./docs/secrets-and-local-config.md:139:The frontend never receives the Gemini API key. The browser only talks to the FastAPI backend, and all Gemini access stays in backend-owned services and adapters.\n./backend/migrations/script.py.mako:10:from alembic import op\n./backend/app/worker/README.md:3:This package is reserved for durable background job execution.\n./backend/app/worker/README.md:5:Future prompts should place composition, narration, and other long-running workflow workers here instead of embedding that logic in HTTP route handlers.\n./docs/adr/README.md:9:- `0001-core-runtime-architecture.md`: backend-owned AI calls, durable Postgres session state, file-backed GCS assets, websocket live updates, separate workers for long-running jobs, and soft planning constraints\n./docs/realtime-events.md:83:  \"type\": \"job.progress\",\n./docs/realtime-events.md:88:    \"actor_id\": \"worker\"\n./docs/realtime-events.md:125:| `job.progress` | yes | Progress checkpoint for composition or audio jobs. |\n./docs/realtime-events.md:126:| `job.status` | yes | Queue, start, pause, completion, cancellation, or failure transition for a job. |\n./docs/realtime-events.md:127:| `error.notification` | yes | User-visible session or job error that should survive replay. |\n./docs/realtime-events.md:178:- `job_id`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:205:### `job.progress`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:210:- `job_id`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:211:- `job_kind`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:230:- `job_kind` is `composition` or `audio`.\n./docs/realtime-events.md:231:- `status` mirrors the durable job states: `queued`, `in_progress`, `paused`,\n./docs/realtime-events.md:234:  both job kinds so the transport stays uniform.\n./docs/realtime-events.md:238:### `job.status`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:243:- `job_id`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:244:- `job_kind`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:271:- `job_id`\n./docs/realtime-events.md:272:- `job_kind`\n./backend/migrations/env.py:6:from alembic import context\n./backend/app/models/session.py:91:    job_kind: str\n./backend/app/models/session.py:175:    active_composition_job: CompositionJobView | None = None\n./backend/app/models/session.py:176:    active_audio_job: AudioJobView | None = None\n./prompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.md:10:- Write an ADR or equivalent note for the main architectural choices: backend-owned AI calls, Postgres-backed durable state, file-backed GCS emulator for assets, WebSocket-based live updates, and a separate worker process for long-running jobs.\n./prompts/09-initial-system-diagram-and-adr.md:11:- Add one lightweight system diagram in Markdown or Mermaid showing browser, API, worker, database, object storage, and Gemini integrations.\n./prompts/91-rate-limits-retries-and-fallbacks.md:7:Harden the app against transient Gemini failures, quota issues, and worker retries so long workflows do not fail messily.\n./prompts/91-rate-limits-retries-and-fallbacks.md:12:- Expose clear job status and chat or UI messages when the system is waiting, retrying, or needs user intervention.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:45:- composition jobs and segment progress\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:46:- audio jobs and segment progress\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:66:- WebSockets handle session progress, job status, and incremental event delivery.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:71:### 5. Long-running generation runs in a separate worker process\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:73:Composition and audio generation run in a worker process that is separate from the API process.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:75:- API routes create or update durable job records.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:76:- Workers claim pending jobs, call Gemini or narration providers, persist partial outputs, and append durable events.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:99:- Later prompts have a clear split between API responsibilities and worker responsibilities.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:103:- The system is more complex than a single FastAPI process with synchronous handlers.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:104:- Websocket delivery and worker orchestration add coordination work that later prompts must implement carefully.\n./docs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:105:- Developers need to think about job state transitions and event ordering early.\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:34:  - `composition_job_id`\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:36:  - `audio_job_id`\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:82:- ownership validation for linked composition/audio jobs,\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:84:- inferred parent composition job linkage when only a composition segment is provided,\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:85:- validation that `audio_segment` assets include both `audio_job_id` and `segment_index`,\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:86:- validation that `final_audio` assets belong to an `audio_job`,\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:160:    composition_job_id=composition_job_id,\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:183:- parent `composition_job_id`\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:197:    audio_job_id=audio_job_id,\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:202:The service deliberately requires `audio_job_id` and `segment_index` here so segmented narration output stays queryable and ordered.\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:362:- `final_audio` assets should always belong to an `audio_job`. I enforced that in the new asset service.\n./prompts/16-asset-metadata-and-file-records.summary.md:364:- `composition_segment` assets may reasonably infer their parent `composition_job_id` from the linked `composition_segment`.\n./backend/migrations/versions/20260331_03_generalize_export_assets_to_session_assets.py:10:from alembic import op\n./backend/migrations/versions/20260331_03_generalize_export_assets_to_session_assets.py:62:        sa.Column(\"composition_job_id\", sa.String(length=36), nullable=True),\n./backend/migrations/versions/20260331_03_generalize_export_assets_to_session_assets.py:64:        sa.Column(\"audio_job_id\", sa.String(length=36), nullable=True),\n./backend/migrations/versions/20260331_03_generalize_export_assets_to_session_assets.py:86:            [\"audio_job_id\"],\n./backend/migrations/versions/20260331_03_generalize_export_assets_to_session_assets.py:87:            [\"audio_jobs.id\"],\n./backend/migrations/versions/20260331_03_generalize_export_assets_to_session_asse