{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "failed, exit 1: /bin/zsh -lc 'cd backend && .venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/test_background_jobs.py tests/test_worker_runtime.py tests/test_migrations.py -q'", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": ".F....                                                                   [100%]\n=================================== FAILURES ===================================\n___________ test_background_job_service_tracks_leases_and_completion ___________\n\nsqlite_session_factory = sessionmaker(class_='Session', bind=Engine(sqlite+pysqlite:////private/var/folders/jr/b94rjp3d6hq0f5ycvc20b3mw0000gn/T/pytest-of-kevin/pytest-164/test_background_job_service_tr0/background-jobs.db), autoflush=False, expire_on_commit=False)\n\n    def test_background_job_service_tracks_leases_and_completion(\n        sqlite_session_factory: sessionmaker[Session],\n    ) -> None:\n        with sqlite_session_factory() as session:\n            service = BackgroundJobService(session)\n            queued = service.enqueue_job(\n                job_type=\"demo.echo\",\n                payload={\"message\": \"hello\", \"steps\": 2},\n            )\n    \n        assert queued.status == JobStatus.QUEUED\n        assert queued.attempt_count == 0\n        assert queued.lease_owner is None\n    \n        with sqlite_session_factory() as session:\n            service = BackgroundJobService(session)\n            claimed = service.claim_next_job(\n                lease_owner=\"worker-a\",\n                lease_duration=timedelta(seconds=30),\n            )\n    \n        assert claimed is not None\n        assert claimed.job_type == \"demo.echo\"\n        assert claimed.attempt_count == 1\n        assert claimed.lease_owner == \"worker-a\"\n    \n        with sqlite_session_factory() as session:\n            service = BackgroundJobService(session)\n            assert (\n                service.claim_next_job(\n                    lease_owner=\"worker-b\",\n                    lease_duration=timedelta(seconds=30),\n                )\n                is None\n            )\n    \n        with sqlite_session_factory() as session:\n            service = BackgroundJobService(session)\n            heartbeat = service.heartbeat_job(\n                claimed,\n                lease_duration=timedelta(seconds=45),\n            )\n    \n        assert heartbeat.status == JobStatus.IN_PROGRESS\n        assert heartbeat.lease_expires_at is not None\n>       assert heartbeat.lease_expires_at > claimed.lease_expires_at\n               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nE       TypeError: can't compare offset-naive and offset-aware datetimes\n\ntests/test_background_jobs.py:82: TypeError\n=========================== short test summary info ============================\nFAILED tests/test_background_jobs.py::test_background_job_service_tracks_leases_and_completion\n1 failed, 5 passed in 0.43s\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'cd backend && .venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/test_background_jobs.py tests/test_worker_runtime.py tests/test_migrations.py -q'", "exit_code": 1, "id": "item_66", "status": "failed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 129, "prompt_index": 19, "prompt_name": "18 \u2014 Postgres-Backed Job Runner Skeleton", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T00:48:05-07:00"}
{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "The first focused test exposed a SQLite quirk rather than a queue bug: lease datetimes come back timezone-naive from SQLite, while the in-memory claim object is timezone-aware. I\u2019m normalizing that assertion so the test still checks the...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_67", "text": "The first focused test exposed a SQLite quirk rather than a queue bug: lease datetimes come back timezone-naive from SQLite, while the in-memory claim object is timezone-aware. I\u2019m normalizing that assertion so the test still checks the lease extension semantics without depending on backend-specific datetime behavior.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 130, "prompt_index": 19, "prompt_name": "18 \u2014 Postgres-Backed Job Runner Skeleton", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T00:48:18-07:00"}
