{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "The worker now gets past secrets loading, but the live container check exposed a second infrastructure bug: the Compose database URL was using the generic `postgresql://` scheme, which makes SQLAlchemy look for `psycopg2`, while this rep...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_97", "text": "The worker now gets past secrets loading, but the live container check exposed a second infrastructure bug: the Compose database URL was using the generic `postgresql://` scheme, which makes SQLAlchemy look for `psycopg2`, while this repo only installs `psycopg`. I\u2019m normalizing the runtime DSN strings to `postgresql+psycopg://` in the actual execution paths and tests, then I\u2019ll rerun the Compose smoke test.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 184, "prompt_index": 19, "prompt_name": "18 \u2014 Postgres-Backed Job Runner Skeleton", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T00:52:11-07:00"}
